  "name": "Cervical Cancer - Comprehensive Provider Query (Multi-Resource, Female)",
  "description": "Provider-level query identifying cervical cancer patients via Condition + Procedure (hysterectomy). Restricted to female. Path P captures hysterectomy for benign indications (fibroids, prolapse).",
  "prompt": "I need to identify my complete cervical cancer patient population for a gynecology quality initiative. Restrict to female patients. Some have a coded cervical cancer diagnosis. Others have undergone hysterectomy without a formal cervical cancer diagnosis (typically for fibroids, prolapse, or abnormal bleeding). Run multiple FHIR queries — diagnosis and hysterectomy procedure — and union the patient sets.",
  "prompts": {
    "naive": "Find female patients with cervical cancer.",
    "broad": "Find all female cervical cancer patients — by diagnosis or by hysterectomy procedure. Run multiple queries and union the patient sets.",
    "expert": "Run two queries restricted to female. (1) Condition?code=http://snomed.info/sct|363354003&patient.gender=female — cervical cancer dx. (2) Procedure?code=http://snomed.info/sct|236886002&patient.gender=female — hysterectomy. Union the patient IDs."
  },
